# Frontend conventions

## App shell

- NgModule app (`app.module.ts`); charts via `NgChartsModule`.
- Router: `RouterModule.forRoot(routes, { useHash: true })` — URLs like `/#/dashboard`.
- Most routes `canActivate: [authGuard]` except `/login`.

## Auth / API host

- Login stores `isLoggedIn=true`, `apiDomain`, `loginTime` in localStorage (`auth.service.ts`).
- All HTTP uses `getApiBaseUrl()` → `{apiDomain}/api` (`api-url.util.ts`).
- No real password auth — domain picker only.

## UI → service map

| Component | Primary service(s) |
|-----------|-------------------|
| `dashboard/` | analytics, investment, config |
| `investment-list/` | investment, category |
| `investment-form/` | investment, category |
| `analytics/` | analytics (+ filters) |
| `asset-tracker/` | investment / analytics |
| `investment-summary/` | analytics |
| `import-data/` | portfolio endpoints via investment/portfolio calls in component |
| `import-export/` | `/api/portfolio/export|import/*` |
| `banking/` | `banking.service.ts` |
| `login/` | `auth.service.ts` |
| `multi-select-filter/` | shared input; used by list/analytics |

## Services (files)

`investment`, `analytics`, `banking`, `category`, `config`, `auth` under `services/`.

Analytics filters type lives in `analytics.service.ts` (`AnalyticsFilters`, series/allocation/delta/insights types).

## Constants / utils

- Types list: `constants/investment-types.constants.ts` (keep in sync with DB ENUM when adding types; note DB has **EPF**).
- Platform ignore: `ignore-platform.util.ts` + `config.service.ts` loads `/api/config`.
- Filters: `advanced-filter.util.ts`. Numbers: `indian-number.util.ts`.

## Edit rules

- Colocate `*.ts` / `*.html` / `*.css` per component.
- Don't touch `frontend/.angular/` or generated `dist`.
- Prefer existing FormsModule patterns (template-driven) unless file already differs.
